&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deputy Ward Manager - Male Forensic Service at Tamarind Centre&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Opportunities across ICU, acute and rehabilitative care&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also be expected to fulfill the role of the Duty Senior Nurse and work the full range of shift patterns including nights and bank holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for the appointment of Deputy Ward Managers at Tamarind.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit highly motivated individuals, who are passionate about providing high quality and compassionate care in the secure environment, to men who are experiencing complex mental ill health and personality disorders and who demonstrate challenging behavior.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Post holders will assist the Ward Manager in the provision of clinical leadership, driving up and maintaining quality care, and being a positive clinical role model. This will provide an ideal opportunity to extend your skill base in clinical leadership and ward/site management, with opportunities to become involved in a variety of work streams including recruitment, service and staff development and audit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDave Austin / Hazel NdoroJob titleClinical Nurse Manager / MatronTelephone number0121 301 0518 / 0820&lt;/p&gt;
